description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 6 – Subject to Job Matching&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have an exciting opportunity for a band 6 Practice Development Nurses, to work within a new unique team. The team will be led by a band 7 Practice Development Nurse lead. The team and the posts will have an education focus, be situated within the Professional Practice Team, however the successful candidates will be working within clinical practice, supporting and developing clinical staff, increasing the on the job knowledge and expertise. Embedding &amp; assessing clinical skills and competencies &amp; other key clinically focused education requirements will be integral to the roles. Preferably the successful candidates will have prior experience within professional education, current clinical knowledge and experience within medicine, surgery, intermediate care and the community nursing disciplines&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Excellent communication, teaching and presentation skills are a must. Experience of developing education packages and supporting learners would be advantageous.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post is secondment for 18 months&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hours per week: 30&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date: 12th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please be aware that this post requires an Enhanced with Barred list Disclosure and Barring Service (DBS) check, the cost of which is payable by the successful candidate.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you have lived or worked abroad for 6 months or more in the last 5 years you will need to obtain an overseas police clearance. Further information can be found on the additional information links at the bottom of the advert.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;To keep up to date with all of our latest Recruitment activity here at East Cheshire NHS Trust, take a look at our Careers website with lots of information on how to join our team and Facebook and Twitter pages, links to which can be found on the right hand side:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Visit our Facebook page: Careers at East Cheshire NHS Trust&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Follow us on Twitter: @CareersECT&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name Alison Lomas Job title Professional Practice Lead Email address alisonlomas@nhs.net Telephone number 01625 661649&lt;/p&gt;
